# asana — credentials (copy to $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/asana/credentials.env,
# default ~/.config/asana/credentials.env, and fill). This is the tier-3
# (user config) source in the 4-tier cascade:
#   flags > project .env(.local) > THIS user config > process env.
# A consuming project can override per-project by setting these in its own .env.
# PUBLIC REPO: never commit real values. Leave blank here; fill only the copy.

# Asana Personal Access Token — the default identity every call uses.
# Mint one at https://app.asana.com/0/my-apps. Never pass it on the command line.
ASANA_TOKEN=

# Alternate identities (optional). The CLI selects which key holds the PAT with
# `--token-env <KEY>` — e.g. to post a teammate's reply authored as them. Add the
# key here (or in the project .env) and name it on the call; the value never
# touches the command line. Example:
# ASANA_ALT_TOKEN=
